msContents.summary: Commentary on a work of grammar by Ibn Mālik known as the Alfīyah.

title: Sharḥ mukhtaṣar ʻalá Alfīyat Ibn Mālik.

title.#text: شرح مختصر على ألفية ابن مالك

persName.#text: Makkūdī, ʻAbd al-Raḥmān ibn ʻAlī, -1404 or 1405
Ibn Mālik, Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd Allāh, -1274
ابن مالك، محمد بن عبد الله،

msItem.title: Sharḥ mukhtaṣar ʻalá Alfīyat Ibn Mālik.

supportDesc.extent: xvii, 179, xx foliated leaves : 215 x 170 (140 x 100) mm bound to 215 x 180 x 50 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto (except f. 2, which is marked on verso); catchwords lower left versos.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribī script using brown ink.

decoNote: Rubrications mostly in red, but also in blue, green and purple.

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard (Type III); blind-stamped central mandorla with two pendants on the vertical axis, borders, and frame; plain paper doublure.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Alexander I. Cotheal (stamps, f. 1r, 178v).

term: Ibn Mālik, Muḥammad ibn ʻAbd Allāh,---1274--Alfīyah
